The paper discusses the security of a DNS query obfuscation scheme, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The scheme is evaluated in a real-world web surfing scenario, which involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses practical challenges, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and social implications (cs.SI).
